{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KNRL3wVbE39hg5cnDfVxaj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bilingual test (Faszerowana papryka) is now failing. Fix B added protection for the structural heading, but that's causing `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM` (which IS the structural heading) to be preserved instead of suppressed.\n\nThe issue: `firstStructuralHeading` is `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM` in this test case. Fix B protects it from suppression, but in the bilingual case we actually WANT it suppressed so that `Faszerowana papryka` wins.\n\nThe improvement plan acknowledged this risk:\n> **Risk:** Low. In the legitimate bilingual case (Faszerowana papryka), the structural heading is `\"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"` — but that case is handled by the position-0 mixed-case title `\"Faszerowana papryka\"` winning via threshold after suppression. The guard would preserve `\"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"` in `scoredForThreshold`, but since `\n\n\"Faszerowana papryka\"` also remains and wins via position factor + being the threshold leader after ALL_CAPS suppression, the final result is unchanged. **Verify this claim by running the test suite.**\n\nThe prediction was wrong—Fix B breaks the test. The real issue is that Fix A (the pipe filter) should handle the CHLEBEK case on its own by excluding `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` entirely, preventing bilingual detection from triggering. Fix B's approach is fundamentally flawed for this scenario.\n\nLooking at the actual test case, when `firstStructuralHeading` is `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM`, Fix B shields it from suppression, keeping it in the threshold calculation. With its ALL_CAPS bonus plus structural heading bonus, it could outscore `Faszerowana papryka`, causing the bilingual test to fail. The improvement plan underestimated this risk. Since Fix A alone solves the CHLEBEK case, I should skip Fix B entirely rather than risk breaking the other test.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,